parameters:
"Dyuhuhu, you've finally arrived. I've been waiting for
you."

"It's futile. This test subject will no longer listen to
anyone's voice but mine."

"Dyuhuhu, that's right. But you know, I've grown tired of
collecting data from this pig."

"And then, dyuhuh, dyuhuhuh!! Just when I heard a new test
subject wandered in at the perfect time."
"Oh yes, I definitely thought I should get my hands on it."

"Dyuhuh!! Even if a test subject forgives me, in the end,
you'll also become a toy that spouts data while oinking
away."
"Heheh, then shall we begin at once?"

"Dyuhuhuh, isn't it wonderful? I've thoroughly brainwashed
Tina-chan and layered on a powerful enslavement contract!!"

"Suelle, I understand how you feel, but focus on what you
need to do to help our friend."
"Yeah, I understand. Tina, I'm going to save you now."

Selphie's bullets ricochet off the walls, aiming for any
opening in Tina's defense, shooting wildly from all
directions.

However, Tina deflects the bullets without even looking at
them, accurately bouncing them back towards Selphie.
"(But she's too focused on my bullets.)"

Selphie wasn't trying to hit Tina with her attack. She was
moving to create an opening that Tina couldn't be aware of
due to the ricocheting bullets.
With a loud bang, Suelle fires bullets towards Tina.

The special bullets that Nolz used on the brainwashed girl,
Ameri. If hit, they would interfere with the spell commands
and temporarily disable her with their special attack
properties.

Tina hadn't expected Suelle, who lacked combat strength, to
participate in the fight. No, she had been led to believe
that he wouldn't participate, so he waited for the perfect
moment to strike.

Still, if Suelle had even a little bit of skill in combat,
Tina would have paid some attention to him.

But that's exactly why this surprise attack was so effective
because it was believed that Suelle had no place in combat.
This surprise attack was maximally effective.

"(It's a complete surprise attack from outside her
awareness!!)"
The bullet should have hit Tina and stopped her movement.

Just as if it were a natural, automatic response, she
precisely deflects Suelle's bullet.

An absolutely superior and top-class defense skill that
invalidates any surprise attacks.

Suelle didn't seem to think anything would change just
because Tina deflected the bullet.

No, in reality, it would normally be impossible to change
the course of a battle with just one bullet against Tina.

"But, her consciousness will be disrupted, creating a
momentary opening!!"

Just for a moment, a gap so brief that Suelle couldn't even
perceive it.

But the one fighting now is Selphie. A genius with combat
abilities on par with Tina in the Hero Party.

To ordinary people, such a brief gap would be imperceptible,
but for Selphie, it becomes a significant advantage.
Selphie releases a full-powered shot aimed at Tina.

It's not a ricocheting bullet or one with special movements.
It's a simple trajectory that pierces the shortest straight
line.

Against Selphie, who is neither an unsuspecting non-
combatant nor caught off guard, Tina's Full Body does not
activate.

However, precisely because it doesn't activate, Tina doesn't
lose consciousness and still shows a super reaction that
surpasses perfection to Selphie's attack under these
circumstances.

Of course. Tina is a member of the Hero Party that defeated
the Demon Lord. A battle isn't decided by exploiting such a
small opening.

She swings her sword to directly deflect the bullet back at
Selphie.
"That's right, the angle of that slash..."

"You absolutely thought I would deflect your attack back at
you."

Tina's defense is to deflect and convert it into an attack.
That's Tina's preferred method of attack.

The more she's cornered, the more this habit shows. It was
something only a comrade who had fought alongside her for
years would understand.
\C[2]"I can dodge the bullet you deflect."\C[0]

Tina also knows that Selphie can dodge it. The purpose is to
use the time Selphie dodges to regain her stance and reset.

But Tina had overlooked one thing. No, she couldn't notice
it because she had used Full Body on Suelle.

The moment of unconsciousness with Full Body, the place
where Selphie had moved to.

Selphie: "\C[2]That Maroges is in the line of fire where I
dodged.\C[0]"

Suddenly, Tina's strength drains from her body, and she
collapses.

"Phew, it worked. I had various patterns in mind, but it was
successful."

"It's the contract of servitude. You were the one who
mentioned it first, weren't you?"

"You said to stack a powerful contract of servitude so that
one cannot resist."

"So if the master is attacked, the effect that makes one
lose their strength becomes strongly activated, right?"

"And unless you release it, it will never be undone. Isn't
that right?"

"Now, what will you do? Of course, I won't let you perform
the release spell to make Tina able to move again."
"She was never yours to begin with."
"The floor just opened!! Does this mean... "
"Calm down. That was made for escaping."

"If we chase him recklessly now, we'll activate traps
designed to prevent pursuit and won't be able to catch up."

"Besides, we need to help Tina now. That's our priority,
right?"

"Yeah, you're right. I almost jumped into a trap leaving
Tina behind."
"Tina, I'm going to release you from the brainwashing now."
